                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Exercises-To-Strengthen-Your-Lower-Back.jpeg","7 Great Exercises To Strengthen Your Lower Back","Do you ever find it difficult to bend forward because of low back pain? What about if you sit for extended periods of time? Or have you noticed yourself rubbing your achy, lower back lately when in standing position, wishing for bed rest? How about wishing you could lift your little one, a suitcase, or even a bag of groceries to shoulder height more easily? If you answered “yes” to any of the above, you might benefit from workouts that help strengthen your lower back.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/7-great-exercises-to-strengthen-your-lower-back/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/How-To-Get-Started-In-The-Gym-sm.jpg","Beginner Strength Workout – How To Get Started In The Gym","If you’re a new member at Anytime Fitness, welcome! We’re so happy you’re here. You’re about to embark on a journey that will help you become a healthier and happier version of yourself. And who wouldn’t want that? The hardest part of any fitness journey is making the decision to make healthy happen, and you’ve already done that, so great job!","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/beginner-strength-workout-how-to-get-started-in-the-gym/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/trx-workout-sm.jpg","The Only Full Body TRX Workout You’ll Need","Whether you’re new to the gym or a seasoned vet, you’ve likely seen those colorful straps hanging around and wondered, “What in the world are those?” or “I know what they are but can I really get a great workout with them?” Well, you’re in luck, because we are about to answer both those questions.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/the-only-body-trx-workout-youll-need/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/emom-strength-builder-sm.jpg","EMOM Strength Builder","Have you heard of EMOM? No, we don’t mean a digital mother—we’re talking about an Every-Minute-On-the-Minute-style workout. What does an EMOM workout entail? It means that you’ll work at the top of every minute and once the reps are completed, you’ll rest for the remainder of the minute. Your rest time will be dependent on how quickly or slowly you work through the reps.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/emom-strength-builder/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/20-Minute%E2%80%AFBodyweight-Energy%E2%80%AFWorkout.jpg","20-Minute Bodyweight Energy Workout","This workout will leave you feeling energized and put a spring in your step. You’ll learn how to do a Turkish Get-Up and meet Coach Rachel’s dog, Soka, when she decides to stop by and say hello. Get ready to feel the burn with two rounds of 45 seconds/work and 15 seconds/rest with each exercise. Don’t worry about grabbing any equipment, bodyweight is all you’ll need!","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/20-min-bodyweight-energy-workout/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/ladder-strength-training-sm.jpg","Ladder-Style Strength Training","In order to join Coach Rachel with this incrementally challenging workout, you will need one weight or other piece of equipment with a handle! However, there are no “ladders” involved. A ladder-style workout indicates that you will progressively add reps until you hit a certain point, for today—that point is five—and decrease reps in the same fashion to finish. Feel free to move at your own pace but try your best to stick with it through the end.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/ladder-style-strength-training/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/energy-booster-refresh-sm.jpg","Energy Booster Refresh","This  Energy Booster workout is comprised of four simple movements that will activate, open, and align your body, led by Coach Katie. These moves are perfect for pre-performance, cool down, or a midday break to get the oxygen flowing. Whether you spend the majority of your day seated or you find yourself standing often, these movements are a great way to re-center your posture, your breath and get your blood pumping.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/energy-booster-refresh/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.anytimefitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Resistance-Band-Strength-Training-1536x1021.jpeg","Resistance Band Strength Training Workout","Dust off your resistance bands (or grab your weights) and get ready to sweat with Coach Rachel! This fun workout will help you build strength through resistance, but don’t worry. If you don’t have resistance bands or weights, grab a few cans from the pantry and let’s make healthy happen! Just make sure that the objects you hold have equal weight so that your movements are symmetrical and work each side in the same way.","https://www.anytimefitness.com/ccc/workouts/resistance-band-strength-training-workout/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/everyone-can-reap-the-benefits-of-physical-activity.png","Everyone can reap the benefits of physical activity, regardless of age, shape or size.","Regular physical activity is one of the most important things you can do for your health. Being physically active can improve your brain health, help manage weight, reduce the risk of disease, strengthen bones and muscles, and improve your ability to do everyday activities.","https://www.cdc.gov/physicalactivity/basics/pa-health/index.htm#LiveLonger"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/regular-physical-activity-can-help-prevent-manage-diabetes.png","Regular physical activity, combined with a healthy diet, can help prevent and manage Type 2 Diabetes.","In this article, the broader term “physical activity” (defined as “bodily movement produced by the contraction of skeletal muscle that substantially increases energy expenditure”) is used interchangeably with “exercise,” which is defined as “a subset of PA done with the intention of developing physical fitness (i.e., cardiovascular [CV], strength, and flexibility training).”","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2992225/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/an-hour-of-exercise-a-day-goes-a-long-way.png","An hour of exercise a day goes a long way.","Regular physical activity is one of the most important things you can do for your health. Being physically active can improve your brain health, help manage weight, reduce the risk of disease, strengthen bones and muscles, and improve your ability to do everyday activities.","https://www.cdc.gov/physicalactivity/basics/pa-health/index.htm#LiveLonger"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/regular-physical-exercise-can-help-you-sleep-better.png","Regular physical exercise can help you sleep better.","You know exercise is good for you, but do you know how good? From boosting your mood to improving your sex life, find out how exercise can improve your life.","https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/fitness/in-depth/exercise/art-20048389?pg=2"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/working-out-regularly-shrinks-your-fat-cells.png","Working out regularly shrinks your fat cells.","As millions of people enter 2020 with a new resolve to slim down, they have a pesky physiological fact to contend with: No matter how much weight they lose, the number of fat cells in their bodies will likely never actually decrease.","https://www.discovermagazine.com/health/your-fat-cells-never-disappear-making-future-weight-gain-more-likely"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/10-percent-of-people-are-successful-at-losing-weight-through-diet.png","Only 10% of people are successful at losing weight through diet alone.","The two major players in the weight-loss battle are diet and exercise. But can the battle be won using only one of these tools? Many people opt for the easier route, which they believe is dieting. But when you consider how poor the statistics are for long-term weight loss through diets, you need to consider a combination of both.","https://www.acefitness.org/resources/everyone/blog/6708/weight-loss-diet-vs-exercise/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/exercise-has-an-antidepressant-effect.png","Exercise has an antidepressant effect on those suffering from clinical depression.","Millions of Americans suffer from clinical depression each year. Most depressed patients first seek treatment from their primary care providers. Generally, depressed patients treated in primary care settings receive pharmacologic therapy alone. There is evidence to suggest that the addition of cognitive-behavioral therapies, specifically exercise, can improve treatment outcomes for many patients.","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC474733/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/regular-exercise-can-help-reduce-symptoms-of-anxiety.png","Living with anxiety? Regular exercise can help reduce the symptoms of the condition.","The beneficial effects of regular physical activity on health are indisputable in the field of modern medicine. Exercise is often the first step in lifestyle modifications for the prevention and management of chronic diseases. According to a US Department of Health and Human Services report on physical activity, regular exercise significantly reduced causes of mortality by up to 30% for men and women (DHHS, 2002).","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3632802/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/30-percent-of-adults-feel-less-stressed-after-exercising.png","30% of adults report feeling less stressed after exercising.","For over a decade, the American Psychological Association (APA) has commissioned an annual nationwide survey as part of its Mind/Body Health campaign to examine the state of stress across the country and understand its impact.","https://www.tnchiro.com/research/8-statistics-show-exercise-is-a-healthy-stress-reliever-for-teens-and-adults/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/not-exercising-regularly-results-in-muscle-loss.png","People who don’t regularly exercise could lose up to 80% of their muscle strength by age 65.","When someone performs an exercise routine consistently there are many positive health results. The following are a few interesting facts about exercise: 1.A pound of muscle burns three times more calories than a pound of fat. 2.Having more muscle than fat means you can consume more calories. 3.The average person walks about 7,500 steps per day. If you stick to that average step count and live to be 80 years old, you’ll walk about 110,000 miles in your lifetime. 4.People who do the same daily type of exercise regularly are more prone to injury. 5.People who don’t regularly exercise may lose up to 80% of their muscle strength by age 65. 6.Physical activity is an important way to prevent heart disease (the nation’s No. 1 killer) and stroke (the nation’s No. 5 killer). 7.There is no difference in power output between working out with or without music. 8.Nicotine use may produce beneficial effects for anaerobic exercise. In particularly, peak power output and average power seemed to improve with nicotine use.  Please don’t smoke to get your nicotine fix.","https://ace-pt.org/fun-exercise-facts/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/a-quarter-of-adults-arent-active-at-all.png","A quarter of adults aren’t active at all.","Consistency is the key to maintaining a healthy lifestyle, right? But how do you know when it's time to change your routine? While consistency is good, there are a few signs that may indicate that it’s time to change your current workout.","https://www.acefitness.org/resources/everyone/blog/6244/when-is-it-time-to-change-your-workout/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/80-percent-who-have-a-gym-membership-do-not-use-the-gym.png","80% of Americans who have a gym membership do not use the gym.","The gym is about more than just exercise. Find out 9 surprising stats which might just make you think differently about that gym membership.","https://www.realbuzz.com/articles-interests/fitness/article/9-surprising-gym-statistics/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/only-1-in-5-children-do-enough-physical-exercise.png","Only one in five children around the world do enough physical exercise.","Four in five 11- to 17-year-olds around the world are not taking enough physical exercise, according to the first such analysis. The World Health Organization says children's health is being damaged as well as their brain development and social skills. It says failing to take the recommended hour a day of exercise is a universal problem in rich and poor countries. Boys were more active than girls in all but four of the 146 countries studied.","https://www.bbc.com/news/health-50466061"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/10-minutes-of-exercise-will-help-raise-your-heart-rate.png","Pinched for time? Even 10 minutes of exercise will help raise your heart rate and maintain fitness levels.","Exercise is not just about aerobic capacity and muscle size. Sure, exercise can improve your physical health and your physique, trim your waistline, improve your sex life, and even add years to your life. But that’s not what motivates most people to stay active.","https://www.helpguide.org/articles/healthy-living/the-mental-health-benefits-of-exercise.htm"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/walking-is-the-most-popular-way-to-stay-active.png","Walking is the most popular way to stay active in the United States.","People living in the Pacific, New England, and Mountain regions of the country are more likely to participate in sports or exercise activities than those in other regions. In fact, those living in the Pacific region are about 50 percent more likely to exercise on an average day than are those in the East South Central and West South Central regions.","https://www.bls.gov/spotlight/2008/sports/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/walking-can-burn-almost-as-many-calories-as-jogging-.png","Walking at a brisk pace can burn almost as many calories as jogging the same distance.","Walking at a brisk pace (a 15-minute mile or 4 mph) burns almost as many calories as jogging for the same distance. The benefit of jogging is that it takes less time to cover the same distance and it benefits the bones; however, it may be too strenuous for some.","https://health.howstuffworks.com/wellness/diet-fitness/information/10-fitness-facts-women-should-know.htm#pt9"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/swimming-incorporates-both-cardio-and-strength-training.png","Swimming is a great form of exercise because it incorporates both cardio and strength training.","National guidelines for a healthy heart suggest getting at least 150 minutes of moderate physical activity each week.  Swimming is a great way to incorporate both strength building and aerobic activity into your fitness routine while going easy on the joints.  April is adult learn to swim month, and a great time to learn about the benefits of swimming and how to get started.","https://bostonheartdiagnostics.com/news/why-you-should-incorporate-swimming-into-your-fitness-routine/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/it-takes-the-body-6-to-8-weeks-to-adapt-to-an-exercise-program.png","It takes the body six to eight weeks to adapt to an exercise program.","change can be a good thing. In fact, varying your exercise routine can have a number of benefits, including preventing boredom and avoiding plateau.","https://www.acefitness.org/resources/everyone/blog/33/should-i-change-up-my-workout-routine/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/the-core-includes-muscles-that-attach-to-your-pelvis-spine-ribs.png","The ‘core’ includes any muscles that attach to your pelvis, spine and ribs.","One of my favorite annual events is the Can-Fit-Pro fitness conference and trade show. I hang out with friends, attend heath related lectures, and buy new fitness gadgets. A fitness instructor's heaven! Every year I think fitness enthusiasts would want to know this stuff!","https://www.huffpost.com/archive/ca/entry/8-fun-fit-facts_b_3889711"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/regular-weight-training-increases-calories-burned.png","Regular weight training increases the number of calories burned during normal activities.","Strength training goes a long way in terms of supporting bone health, making aerobic exercise more productive, preventing injury, and facilitating healthy aging.","https://www.everydayhealth.com/fitness/add-strength-training-to-your-workout.aspx"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/crunches-alone-wont-slim-the-midsection.png","Crunches alone won’t slim the midsection; if you want a flat belly you’ll need to incorporate cardio to burn those calories!","It is easy to feel lost in the sea of suggestions when it comes to addressing abdominal fat. But you are not alone. Everyone wonders what they can do to reduce their fat around the midsection as well as questions whether or not the things they are doing are even working.","https://www.verywellfit.com/can-i-reduce-belly-fat-with-sit-ups-3495613"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/being-fit-makes-your-heart-and-cardiovascular-system-function.png","Being fit is good for your heart because it strengthens the muscles needed to make your heart and cardiovascular system function.","Want to be sharper at work? Feel less tired at home? Spend some quality time with your spouse? How about enjoying a cookie without guilt? If you answered " ,"https://www.webmd.com/men/features/exercise-benefits#1"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/gardening-can-be-an-effective-way-to-build-strength.png","Gardening can be an effective way to build strength throughout your body.","There is increasing evidence that exposure to plants and green space, and particularly to gardening, is beneficial to mental and physical health, and so could reduce the pressure on NHS services. Health professionals should therefore encourage their patients to make use of green space and to work in gardens, and should pressure local authorities to increase open spaces and the number of trees, thus also helping to counteract air pollution and climate change.","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6334070/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/muscle-mass-diminishes-in-middle-age.png","Muscle mass diminishes at the rate of 1% a year in middle age.","A growing body of research shows that working out with weights has health benefits beyond simply bulking up one’s muscles and strengthening bones. Studies are finding that more lean muscle mass may allow kidney dialysis patients to live longer, give older people better cognitive function, reduce depression, boost good cholesterol, lessen the swelling and discomfort of lymphedema after breast cancer and help lower the risk of diabetes.","https://www.latimes.com/health/la-xpm-2011-feb-13-la-he-adv-strength-training-20110213-story.html"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/people-who-work-out-with-a-partner.png","People who work out with a partner are more likely to stick with their fitness regimes.","What if we told you there was a simple trick for totally smashing your health and fitness goals, whether that’s practising better eating habits, getting fitter or running your first big race? Well, according to experts, it lies in finding yourself a sidekick or support group.","https://www.womenshealthmag.com/uk/fitness/workouts/a26338056/accountability-weightwatchers/"))

