                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/crunches-alone-wont-slim-the-midsection.png","Crunches alone won’t slim the midsection; if you want a flat belly you’ll need to incorporate cardio to burn those calories!","It is easy to feel lost in the sea of suggestions when it comes to addressing abdominal fat. But you are not alone. Everyone wonders what they can do to reduce their fat around the midsection as well as questions whether or not the things they are doing are even working.","https://www.verywellfit.com/can-i-reduce-belly-fat-with-sit-ups-3495613"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/being-fit-makes-your-heart-and-cardiovascular-system-function.png","Being fit is good for your heart because it strengthens the muscles needed to make your heart and cardiovascular system function.","Want to be sharper at work? Feel less tired at home? Spend some quality time with your spouse? How about enjoying a cookie without guilt? If you answered ","https://www.webmd.com/men/features/exercise-benefits#1"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/gardening-can-be-an-effective-way-to-build-strength.png","Gardening can be an effective way to build strength throughout your body.","There is increasing evidence that exposure to plants and green space, and particularly to gardening, is beneficial to mental and physical health, and so could reduce the pressure on NHS services. Health professionals should therefore encourage their patients to make use of green space and to work in gardens, and should pressure local authorities to increase open spaces and the number of trees, thus also helping to counteract air pollution and climate change.","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6334070/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/muscle-mass-diminishes-in-middle-age.png","Muscle mass diminishes at the rate of 1% a year in middle age.","Strength training has strong-armed its way beyond the realm of bodybuilding. A growing body of research shows that working out with weights has health benefits beyond simply bulking up one’s muscles and strengthening bones. Studies are finding that more lean muscle mass may allow kidney dialysis patients to live longer, give older people better cognitive function, reduce depression, boost good cholesterol, lessen the swelling and discomfort of lymphedema after breast cancer and help lower the risk of diabetes.","https://www.latimes.com/health/la-xpm-2011-feb-13-la-he-adv-strength-training-20110213-story.html"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/people-who-work-out-with-a-partner.png","People who work out with a partner are more likely to stick with their fitness regimes.","What if we told you there was a simple trick for totally smashing your health and fitness goals, whether that’s practising better eating habits, getting fitter or running your first big race? Well, according to experts, it lies in finding yourself a sidekick or support group.","https://www.womenshealthmag.com/uk/fitness/workouts/a26338056/accountability-weightwatchers/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/scheduling-in-rest-days-gives-your-body-time-to-recover.png","Scheduling in rest days gives your body the time it needs to recover and improve.","Since they don't burn off a lot of calories","https://edition.cnn.com/2014/03/21/health/fitness-myths-busted/index.html"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/it-takes-12-weeks-before-you-start-to-see-measurable-changes.png","It takes 12 weeks of an exercise routine before you start to see measurable changes to your body.","Getting in shape? Learn 10 fitness facts that will help motivate you to get moving. See the next page to get started.","https://health.howstuffworks.com/wellness/diet-fitness/information/10-fitness-facts-women-should-know.htm#pt10"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/music-can-inadvertently-get-you-moving-faster.png","Music can inadvertently get you moving faster during those tough workouts.","Ask a personal trainer how to adjust the treadmill or elliptical to increase intensity. Perhaps try an incline position or hike along uneven terrain. As for engaging your mind, experiment with the visualization for which Zen Master Thich Nhat Hanh is famous. Imagine your feet kissing the earth with each step, and leaving behind beautiful blossoms in your path. An eco-friendly footprint, indeed.","https://fitnessandwellnessnews.com/fun-facts-about-fitness/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/optimal-fitness-requires-a-balanced-exercise-routine.png","Optimal fitness requires a balanced exercise routine that incorporates aerobic, strength training and flexibility exercises.","Getting in shape? Learn 10 fitness facts that will help motivate you to get moving. See the next page to get started.","https://health.howstuffworks.com/wellness/diet-fitness/information/10-fitness-facts-women-should-know.htm#pt8"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/setting-a-goal-helps-you-adhere-to-an-exercise-program.png","Setting a goal is proven to help you adhere to an exercise program.","The aim of the study was to utilize a goal‐setting intervention to examine the impact on motivation and adherence during a six‐week exercise program. Sixty recreational exercisers (M age = 31.17, SD age = 11.77; 33 Males; 27 Females) were randomly assigned to a process goal group (n = 15), an outcome goal group (n = 15), and a no‐goal control group (n = 30).","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/254301548_Effect_of_Goal_Setting_on_Motivation_and_Adherence_in_a_Six-Week_Exercise_Program"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/fitness-influencers-impact-the-health-behaviours-of-young-women.png","Fitness influencers have been shown through research to impact the health behaviours of young women.","The growth of the fitness industry observed in the last decade has been accompanied by the emergence of an occupation as a social media fitness influencer. The most popular are able to accumulate millions of followers. The marketing potential of fitness influencers is a subject of interest, not only for the fitness industry but also for other sectors offering products related to health, wellness, or healthy nutrition.","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7503997/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/exercise-is-important-from-a-young-age.png","Exercise is important from a young age.","With childhood obesity increasing at staggering rates, parents and caregivers must play an active role in protecting children’s health. Eating healthy foods is a key factor in maintaining their overall well-being. But, this has to be balanced with regular physical activity.","https://www.pbs.org/parents/thrive/motivating-kids-to-get-fit"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/youre-never-too-old-for-exercise.png","You’re never too old for exercise.","You know you should exercise. But how do you keep up your dedication to the gym or a training routine when your schedule is overloaded with a million other things, from work to household responsibilities to travel and other social engagements? Or how do you push yourself to start working out if it’s been years (or basically forever) since you last had a good self-imposed sweat?","https://www.everydayhealth.com/fitness/9-simple-tricks-help-you-start-working-out-actually-stick-it/#10"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/18-34-year-olds-are-the-most-likely-to-exercise.png","People aged between 18 and 34 are the most likely to exercise.","When it comes to fitness statistics, there’s a lot to unpack! It’s a fact that not enough of us get the recommended amount of exercise each week. In this article you can learn more about that, plus find out the fittest state and the global challenge to get more people moving.","https://www.thegoodbody.com/fitness-statistics/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/only-half-aged-12-21-exercise-vigorously-on-a-regular-basis.png","Only half of Americans aged 12-21 years exercise vigorously on a regular basis.","This website is archived for historical purposes and is no longer being maintained or updated.","https://www.cdc.gov/nccdphp/sgr/adoles.htm"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/teens-who-exercise-decrease-their-chance-of-developing-a-brain-tumor.png","Teens who exercise decrease their chance of developing a glioma brain tumor by a third compared to those who do not exercise.","Whether energy balance during early life and/or adulthood is related to glioma risk is unknown. We therefore investigated height, body mass index (BMI), and physical activity in relation to glioma risk in the prospective NIH-AARP Diet and Health Study. Participants completed a baseline questionnaire (sent in 1995-1996) inquiring about height, weight, and potential confounders.","https://aacrjournals.org/cancerres/article/69/21/8349/552471/Height-Body-Mass-Index-and-Physical-Activity-in"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/men-have-two-thirds-more-muscle-mass-compared-to-women.png","Men have two-thirds more muscle mass compared to women.","Key Points Most of the major differences in performance and metabolism between sexes can be explained by size and body composition, not biological sex itself. Of the true sex differences, the most important ones have to do with differences in sex hormones and fiber types. Additionally, females’ fat and muscle tissue is better equipped than males’ for handling both carbs and fat. All of these differences make females better metabolically suited for… just about everything related to health and performance except for short, intense bursts of activity that rely on glycolytic capacity. If you prefer pictures to words, the highlights of this article are presented in an infographic at the bottom.","https://www.strongerbyscience.com/gender-differences-in-training-and-diet/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/men-and-women-store-fat-very-differently.png","Men and women store fat very differently.","We all do tend to fatten up with age, although there are interesting differences based on age and gender. Hormones drive the deposition of fat around the pelvis, buttocks, and thighs of women and the bellies of men.","https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/why-does-fat-deposit-on-t/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/during%E2%80%93workouts-women-tend-to-burn-more-fat.png","During workouts, women tend to burn more fat, but post-workout, men burn more fat.","Many people believe that when it comes to weight loss, men have an advantage. Anecdotal stories of ladies sweating and struggling to lose a pound or two compare to tales of men cutting back on the junk, hitting the gym and watching the weight drop off. But what's the real truth?","https://www.webmd.com/diet/features/do-men-lose-weight-faster-than-women#1"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/couples-who-work-out-together-are-more-likely-to-stay-together.png","Couples who work out together are more likely to stay together.","A dream date with your significant other probably does not involve the following: grunting through sets of bench press together, synchronizing your Downward Dog poses in a yoga class, or sprinting side by side to the finish line of a half-marathon. But those very things might be exactly what your body -- and your relationship -- really need.","https://www.webmd.com/fitness-exercise/features/exercise-with-your-significant-other#1"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/a-short-bout-of-exercise-can-improve-your-sex-life.png","Even just a short bout of exercise can drastically improve your sex life!","Obesity and inactivity have led to an increasing number of individuals with sexual dysfunctions (43% of women; 31% of men). Small bouts of exercise can drastically improve sexual functioning. Thus, the present study is designed to examine the effects of physical fitness and self-concept on sexual functioning.","https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5963213/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/people-burns-50-calories%E2%80%93every-hour-while-they-sleep.png","The average person burns 50 calories every hour while they sleep!","Many people are surprised to discover how many calories we burn while sleeping. Although sleeping requires far less energy than most daytime activities, it’s still an active period for our brain and certain other bodily functions.","https://www.sleepfoundation.org/how-sleep-works/how-your-body-uses-calories-while-you-sleep"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/19-percent-have-lied-about-working-out.png","19% of Americans have lied about working out!","According to a survey of 2,000 exercising Americans, 19 percent have lied about working out — and 37 percent admit doing so in order to convince someone else they were busy. That was followed by hoping to impress someone (35 percent) and respondents being embarrassed by what they were actually doing (31 percent).","https://nypost.com/2020/01/13/a-lot-of-americans-lie-about-working-out-to-convince-someone-theyre-busy/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/you-use-200-muscles-when-you-take-a-step.png","You use roughly 200 muscles when you take a single step.","All content of this newsletter is intended for general information purposes only and is not intended or implied to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis or treatment. Please consult a medical professional before adopting any of the suggestions on this page. You must never disregard professional medical advice or delay seeking medical treatment based upon any content of this newsletter. PROMPTLY CONSULT YOUR PHYSICIAN OR CALL 911 IF YOU BELIEVE YOU HAVE A MEDICAL EMERGENCY.","https://jamaicahospital.org/newsletter/how-many-muscles-do-we-use-take-a-single-step-forward/"))

                vlogs.add(HealthVlogs("https://www.thegoodbody.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/the-word-gymnasium-means-school%E2%80%93for-naked-exercise.png","The word ‘gymnasium’ comes from an Ancient Greek term meaning “school for naked exercise”.","gymnasium, large room used and equipped for the performance of various sports. The history of the gymnasium dates back to ancient Greece, where the literal meaning of the Greek word gymnasion was “school for naked exercise.” The gymnasiums were of great significance to the ancient Greeks, and every important city had at least one.","https://www.britannica.com/technology/gymnasium-sports"))

